projectScope.summary:
The Project is an amendment to an existing placer mine (PM19-053) previously assessed by the Designated Office in 2019 (YESAB Project 2019-0116). The proposed amendment includes the addition of 9 claims for a total of 26 claims along Henry Gulch and Hunker Creek, in the Klondike River Watershed.&nbsp;
The project area is located approximately 18 km southeast of Dawson City and is accessed by existing roads. The Project is located within Tr’ondëk Hwëch’in Traditional Territory and falls within both Land Management Unit 11: Goldfields and Land Management Unit 12: Tr’ondëk Täk’it (Klondike Valley) of the Dawson Planning Region. Activities are proposed from May 1 to October 15, annually, until 2030.
Please note, these additional 9 claims are held by another claim holder (Norther Shoveler Resources). The Proponent and Northern Shoveler Resources work together in business and mining related activities. There is an agreement in place for the Proponent to conduct some activities on these claims. These activities are limited to: use of Henry Gulch Creek as a conduit, use of existing settling ponds, withdrawal of water from Hunker Creek and diversion of Henry Gulch Creek.

