projectScope.summary:
The Project is the replacement of the Evelyn Creek and Murphy Creek bridges located at km 43.6 and km 31.4 on the Canol Road, approximately 32 km and 25 km northeast of Johnsons Crossing. The Project lies within the Territory of the Teslin Tlingit Council.
The new bridges will be clear span bridges with no structural footprint in the river and have an expected lifespan of 50 years. No in-stream work is proposed for this project. Bridge replacement activities will occur over one construction season between June 1 and November 30 within the next five years. Bridge replacement activities will occur within the highway right-of-way, the existing Evelyn Creek and Murphy Creek bridgehead reserves (Disposition # 105C14-007 and 105C11-007, respectively), and three gravel pits not currently under a land disposition located at km 21.6, km 38.4 and km 58.7 of Canol Road.&nbsp;
Two camps are proposed within a gravel pit under land disposition #105C11-004, located on the west side at km 3 of Canol Road. Camp 1 will operate for one construction season to support the bridge replacements. Camp 2 will operate from May to February for five construction seasons over the next 15 years to support maintenance or repair activities on Yukon roadways.

