projectScope.summary:
The Project is a placer mining operation located on the right limit bench of the Mayo River valley along Duncan Creek Road, on 42 claims and one prospecting lease.&nbsp;&nbsp;
The Project will be accessed along the Duncan Creek Road via the Silver Trail Highway from Mayo, and is approximately 22 km from Mayo straight-line distance.  Existing roads and trails will be upgraded to facilitate mining. Up to 1 400 m of new roads and 4 700 m of new trails will be developed.&nbsp;
The site is not located directly adjacent to any watercourse, and as such will require storage and pumping to facilitate mining activities.  Water will be sourced from Field Creek, requiring a 2 700 m trail adjacent to the Duncan Creek road, or following the claim boundary.  A pumpline following this trail will and sections of Duncan Creek road will deliver the water to site. To access mining on the south side of Duncan Creek road, the pumpline will cross under the road using a newly installed culvert.  Additional roads will be built on claim between the camp and mining locations to minimize traffic on Duncan Creek road.  One camp will be constructed for up to 8 people. Future exploration and development may occur 200 m to the southeast of Area 2 accessed by a trail, up to 1000 m.
Mining activities will take place between April 1 and November 15, annually, for 10 years.&nbsp;

