projectScope.summary:
Activities under assessment for this project are limited to those proposed for an exploration program; this assessment is not for a mine. Only activities listed below are being assessed for potential environmental and socio-economic effects.
The Proponent is proposing a ground based and heli-supported quartz mineral exploration program on the Kudz Ze Kayah Project, which consists of 879 claims. The Project is accessed via a 24 km tote road from the Robert Campbell Highway and located approximately 110 km southeast of Ross River on the northern edge of the Pelly Mountains. Activities are proposed to occur year-round for five years. The Project is located within the Territories of the Ross River Dena Council and the Liard First Nation.&nbsp;
